  "text": "Prometheus enforces metric naming conventions through a three-layer validation system defined in the prometheus/common/model package and used throughout prometheus/prometheus:\n\n## Metric Name Validation (Snake_case and UTF-8)\n\nThe metric name validation is implemented via the ValidationScheme enum (model.ValidationScheme) which supports two modes:\n- LegacyValidation: Enforces the original Prometheus naming restrictions (alphanumeric, underscore, colon as first character or after alphanumeric)\n- UTF8Validation: Requires only valid UTF-8 strings\n\nThe core validation logic resides in model/labels/labels_common.go where the IsValid() method (line 117-133) calls validationScheme.IsValidMetricName() for the __name__ label. This method checks:\n1. Non-empty string requirement\n2. For legacy mode: restricted character set (alphanumeric, underscore, colon)\n3. For UTF8 mode: valid UTF-8 encoding\n\nMetric name validation is enforced in:\n- model/rulefmt/rulefmt.go (lines 247-251): Recording rule names must be valid metric names\n- model/textparse/protobufparse.go (lines 451-452): Protobuf format metric names validation\n- storage/remote/codec.go (line 854): Remote read/write validation\n\n## Label Name Validation (Alphanumeric and Underscore)\n\nLabel name validation is implemented via validationScheme.IsValidLabelName() which enforces:\n1. Non-empty string requirement\n2. For legacy mode: first character must be letter or underscore, subsequent characters alphanumeric or underscore\n3. For UTF8 mode: valid UTF-8 encoding\n\nLabel name validation is enforced across:\n- model/labels/labels_common.go (line 127): Core label validation in IsValid()\n- model/relabel/relabel.go (lines 140-151): Relabel configuration validation\n- model/rulefmt/rulefmt.go (lines 121, 264, 278): Alert and recording rule label validation\n- config/config.go (line 635): External labels validation\n- promql/engine.go (line 1933): PromQL label_replace validation\n- promql/functions.go (lines 1990-2041): Label manipulation functions validation\n- web/api/v1/api.go (line 843): API endpoint label validation\n- promql/parser/generated_parser.y.go (lines 1439, 1448): Parser label validation\n- storage/remote/codec.go (line 857): Remote protocol label validation\n\n## Help Text Validation (UTF-8)\n\nHelp text presence and validity checks occur during metric exposition format parsing:\n- model/textparse/promparse.go (lines 353-354): Prometheus text format validates help text as valid UTF-8\n- model/textparse/openmetricsparse.go (lines 512-513): OpenMetrics format validates help text as valid UTF-8  \n- model/textparse/protobufparse.go (lines 454-455): Protobuf format validates help text as valid UTF-8\n\n## Validation Scheme Configuration\n\nThe validation scheme is configured globally and can be overridden per-scrape or per-relabel config:\n- config/config.go: Sets MetricNameValidationScheme (default UTF8Validation)\n- scrape configuration can override via metric_name_validation_scheme\n- util/namevalidationutil/namevalidationutil.go: Provides CheckNameValidationScheme() utility\n\nThe ValidationScheme type itself is imported from prometheus/common/model, which defines the enum values (UnsetValidation=0, LegacyValidation=1, UTF8Validation=2) and implements the IsValidMetricName() and IsValidLabelName() methods that are called throughout the codebase."
}

